    "description": "Nichidai Corporation develops, manufactures, and sells precision-forged dies and related forged products in Japan, Thailand, and internationally. It operates through three segments: Molds, Precision Parts, and Filters. The company offers precision forging dies that are used in the production of automotive parts; precision forged parts and assembly of precision parts; and sintered wire mesh filters which are used in the petrochemical, pharmaceutical, and food industries; chemical and nuclear plants; and the H-IIA rocket. In addition, its products include precision forging dies, such as press and former dies; formed products comprising cross joints, inner races, hypoid pinion gears, bevel gears, helical gears, and scrolls; and die sets, including hydraulic enclosing mechanism with pantograph system, hydraulic back pressure, and gas pressure enclosed die sets. Further, the company provides forging DX; precision forgings; and filters, as well as contracted development services. Nichidai Corporation was founded in 1959 and is headquartered in Kyoto, Japan."
